  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When there are lot of unread messages (~100) and the app is opened, the screen freezes for couple of seconds. It can be easily reproducible, even on a relatively powerful phone (Samsung Galaxy S8).  \r\n\r\nIt's not related to the chat screen itself. When Home was the last screen, the app freezes as well. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe UI does not freeze. Instead, it's responsive. User tap should result in UI reaction <100ms according to [76-smooth-ui](https://github.com/status-im/ideas/blob/master/ideas/76-smooth-ui.md)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nWhen there are lot of unread messages and the app is opened, the screen freezes for couple of seconds.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Device A: Create 1-1 chat with another user\r\n- Device A: Put the app into background\r\n- Device B: Send ~100 messages to Device A\r\n- Device A: Click on the last message notification and wait for app to open\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, April 13, TestFairy disabled\r\n* Operating System: Samsung Galaxy S8, Android 7.1",
